This was one of the most healing moments for my dad @sambaldoni and I. 

Thank you all for your love support, compassion and for taking the time to listen to this conversation on this episode of the @wearemanenough podcast. We were both really nervous to talk, and cry like this in public but your response has warmed our hearts and affirmed the reason why we did this.

Here’s to healing. Here’s to being enough.

#ManEnough #Undefined

The kinds of conversations we are having on The Man Enough Podcast—the ones where people go deep and get real about what they do and don’t know, about mistakes they’ve made or are still making, about what it’s been like for them to hurt and be hurting; the conversations that open the door for healing—these are the conversations I have been craving my entire life.
 And something tells me that maybe some of you have too. That's part of why I won't use the term "toxic masculinity" because I've found that too often it ends the conversation instead of deepening it. That's not to say that there aren't unhealthy aspects of how masculinity is expressed and it's also not to say that there aren't systems in place that perpetuate those very aspects. In fact, many of us recognize that we are suffering from the very same problems we helped create, we have just never had the tools to be able to see it or call it out. I want to have conversations that give us those tools.
 
I hope you’ll follow/subscribe to The Man Enough Podcast and come along for the journey with us—the journey from our heads to our hearts, where we attempt to take off some of the masks we’ve been told to wear, and we show up exactly as we are…which is, and always will be, enough.

Link in bio to follow manenough.com/podcast 🎙 @wearemanenough @wayfarerstudios 

#ManEnoughPodcast #Masculinity #UndefiningMyMasculinity @proctergamble

Surprise!!! The Man Enough Podcast is happening!!! So we’ve been secretly recording  for weeks (so hard to keep a surprise) and I’m so excited to announce that it officially launches next Monday, June 21!!
 
Please join me, one of my best friends in the whole world Mr Jamey Heath [@jamey_heath_] and my friend and author the incomparable Liz Plank [@feministabulous] as we dive into honest, raw, and at times uncomfortable conversations with incredible people about what it means to be a man in the world today, but more importantly, what it means to be human.
 
We have some incredible guests in these first episodes! Folks like Matthew McConaughey [@officiallymcconaughey], my spiritual brothers Shawn Mendes [@shawnmendes] and Karamo Brown [@karamo], my idol and book fairy Godmother Glennon Doyle [@glennondoyle], the insanely handsome and funny Eugenio Derbez [@ederbez], two of my best friends @andygrammer and @travisvanwinkle and even my dad (@SamBaldoni) and the love of my life @emilybaldoni (and that’s just to start!) Everyone has been so willing to go deep and take that journey from our head to our heart and our greatest hope is that it invites you to do the same; to learn with us in real time and to increase our capacity for compassion and connection.

New episodes launch every Monday, starting June 21. You can follow/subscribe on your favorite platform or visit ManEnough.com/podcast to find them all. 
 
We will also have the video version of each episode available on the website and the Man Enough YouTube channel. Link in bio!!

Shout out to the amazing team @Cadence13 and our partners @proctergamble for helping bring this podcast to life! Let’s do this!!!
 
#ManEnoughPodcast #ManEnough #Masculinity #UndefiningMyMasculinity

Tune in to hear him talk about grief, masculinity in the Black community, fatherhood, and body image, as well as successfully convincing me I should be getting pedicures. 😉

Lil Rel Howery: Strength in Imperfection
Available Monday, 8/9

node.text:
I’ve never seen her this happy. This much in her element. This much at home. 

With her bare feet planted in the earth, in her nine-sided garden she says her prayers and asks permission to harvest our food with a smile that screams that she’s home. And she is. 

@emilybaldoni is home. My wife is home. 

We had our 8th anniversary this week and in some ways we both feel like in this 9th year we are meeting each other for the first time. Like year nine is really the beginning of our marriage. Like the first eight years was the warm up for this. 

It’s a tremendous amount of mindful work as individuals and as a couple to consciously wipe the generations of dust from each of our mirrors so we can finally see not just ourselves but eachother. And there we are. 

It’s both intense and painful and beautiful and awesome and profound and it’s absolutely worth it.

Who would have thought after eight years of marriage I could rediscover a new type of love for someone I already loved so much. Who would have thought I could re meet my own wife? Who could have thought we could re-meet ourselves. 

Welcome home my love. Thank you for leading the way so I could find home too.

node.text:
Something I’m working harder on now more than I’ve ever worked on anything is allowing myself the time, space and grace to FEEL. I realized that I (like many men) haven’t really ever been allowed to truly feel. So we bottle it up, and sever that connection between our head and our hearts and only give ourselves permission to let our repressed feelings leak as anger or rage. So I’m slowing down and letting myself feel right now. And while it can be uncomfortable, I’m seeing just like a drought, just how much my body has been in need of my tears.

🎧@alifeofgreatnesspodcast
